          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The default implementation of this method does nothing. During the layout cycle, the collection view calls this method first to give you a chance to prepare any data needed during the layout operation. When defining a custom layout, you can override this method and use it to set up data structures or perform any initial computations needed to perform the layout later. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
